---
template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-district-of-columbia
name: OpenAgreements Employee Restrictive Covenant (District of Columbia)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  District of Columbia employee restrictive covenant agreement built for the
  Ban on Non-Compete Agreements Amendment Act of 2020 (D.C. Code
  §§ 32-581.01–.04b): confidentiality and trade-secret protection with the
  statutory information carve-out, an employee non-solicitation covenant, a
  customer non-solicitation covenant, and an optional non-compete confined to a
  highly compensated employee — one at or above the annually indexed minimum
  qualifying annual compensation ($162,164 for most employees in 2026; $270,274
  for a medical specialist). The non-compete recites every § 32-581.03(a)
  validity gate: a stated functional scope and geographic limits, a term of no
  more than 365 calendar days from separation (730 for a medical specialist),
  and delivery of the covenant in writing at least 14 days in advance, with the
  prescribed statutory notice and the workplace-policy disclosure flagged as
  companion writings. For a covered employee below the threshold the covenant is
  banned and void as a matter of law, so the template omits it by default and
  never relies on judicial reformation to cure overbreadth. Drafted as a
  starting point for licensed counsel review.
source_url: >-
  https://github.com/open-agreements/open-agreements/tree/main/templates/openagreements-restrictive-covenant-district-of-columbia
version: 0.1.0
license: CC-BY-4.0
allow_derivatives: true
distribution: bundled
artifact_type: template
